observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Chairman and members of the Bids and Award Committee strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 RIRR of RA No. 9184, specifically the following:

Undertake procurement only if it is included in the approved Annual Procurement Plan;

Invite the three observers in all stages of the procurement activities;


Check the submitted forms of the bidders if compliant with the required mandatory provisions prescribed in the 2016 RIRR of RA No. 9184 and Item 6 of GPPB Circular No. 04-2020;

Require the bidder with the Lowest Calculated Bid to submit its latest income and business tax returns, and other appropriate licenses and permit required by law; and

Require all winning bidders to submit their Construction Schedule and S-curve, Manpower Schedule, Construction Methods, Equipment Utilization Schedule, and DOLE-approved CSHP before approval of their contracts.

The Municipal Mayor to issue directive requiring the Inventory Committee to:
14. Prepare, for his approval, a Physical Inventory Plan containing the assignments of Committee members, schedules/locations and cut-off dates for the complete physical inventory of all properties of the Municipality over a three-month period in CY 2022;
15. Implement the PIP and finish the physical inventory within the time frame specified in CY 2022;
The Inventory Committee to:
16. Consolidate the RPCPPE prepared by each office by grouping together similar items, showing complete data on PPE Type and cost; and
17. Submit the consolidated RPCPPE to the Municipal Accountant before December 31, 2022 for reconciliation, copy furnished the Audit Team.

We recommended that:

The Accounting Office coordinate with the Inventory Committee for the reconciliation of accounting records on inventories and PPE with the RPCI and RPCPPE;

The officers concerned strictly observe the accounting and reporting requirements for the local road network construction and maintenance syste as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015.

We recommended that the City Mayor:
require the Bids and Awards Committee, BAC Secretariat and BAC Technical Working Group to submit all the lacking documents noted to support the propriety of the procurement made by the City Government; and
direct the City Health Officer to ensure that all drugs and medicines to be procured are included in the PNDF, otherwise, a written request with justification should be submitted to the Head of the National Policy Staff for approval of the purchase to avoid disallowance in audit;
